18/05/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Methane gas exploded inside a coal mine in northern Turkey on Monday (May 17th), trapping 32 miners The blast, near the city of Zonguldak on the Black Sea coast, injured 11 others. 
Rescue operations for those stuck 540m below the surface are ongoing. 
Teams are pumping air into the mine and are digging through a collapsed chamber to reach the miners. 
Investigators say the blast was probably caused by an electrical malfunction. 
(AP - 18/05/10; AP, Hurriyet, AFP - 17/05/10)
